From ea6039b389ab8536d876494a4e9e2737d04eb3cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Th=C3=A9o-Paul=20Bodin?= <theo-paul.bodin@softathome.com>
Date: Wed, 19 Feb 2025 17:34:44 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] miniupnpd: add sockopt IP_MULTICAST_LOOP for SSDP Notify
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Problem: Other program on the device doesn't receive broadcasted SSDP Notify message

Cause: IP_MULTICAST_LOOP is set to 0

Solution: set IP_MULTICAST_LOOP to 1 when using AMX backend

Issue: [upnp][discovery] UPnP deviceInstances are not added
after a reboot. [change]

References: PCF-1833, FEAT-13

Signed-off-by: Théo-Paul Bodin <theo-paul.bodin@softathome.com>
---
 miniupnpd/minissdp.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git miniupnpd/minissdp.c miniupnpd/minissdp.c
index 0587e66..1224a88 100644
--- miniupnpd/minissdp.c
+++ miniupnpd/minissdp.c
@@ -291,7 +291,11 @@ static int
 OpenAndConfSSDPNotifySocket(struct lan_addr_s * lan_addr)
 {
 	int s;
+#ifdef USE_AMX
+	unsigned char loopchar = 1;
+#else
 	unsigned char loopchar = 0;
+#endif
 	int bcast = 1;
 	unsigned char ttl = 2; /* UDA v1.1 says :
 		The TTL for the IP packet SHOULD default to 2 and
-- 
2.34.1

